# Copy to .env (gitignored). No secrets are required for a local self-host build —
# gbar's free path lets you paste your own GitHub OAuth App client ID (or a PAT) in
# Settings at runtime, so these can stay blank.
#
# These keys feed the Tuist xcconfigs (Tuist/Config/{Debug,Release}.xcconfig), which
# are materialized — gitignored — from these values by `just bootstrap` (locally) and
# by ci_scripts/ci_post_clone.sh (CI). For local dev you can instead copy the
# *.xcconfig.template files and edit them directly.
#
# GH_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID — a GitHub OAuth App client ID baked into the build so users get
#   one-click "Sign in with GitHub" (device flow, no secret needed). Leave blank for a
#   self-host build; the app will prompt for a client ID / PAT at runtime instead.
#   This is the value the PAID/hosted gbar build ships pre-filled.
# GH_API_BASE_URL — default GitHub API base. Override for GitHub Enterprise.
GH_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID_DEBUG=
GH_API_BASE_URL_DEBUG=https://api.github.com
GH_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID_RELEASE=
GH_API_BASE_URL_RELEASE=https://api.github.com
